		  <div align="center"><img src="http://ghguild.com/forum/upfiles/33/E518F12205974D17BAA2FF5D076C8B2A.jpg" border=0 align="absmiddle"></div><br>
          Posts:  3414<br>
          
          Joined:  10/31/2002 <br>
          
          Status: <span class='offline'>offline</span>
        
		  <img src="image/blank.gif" align="right" border="0" width="155" height="1">
		</td>
        
	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          There are probably special-use cases where raid 0 would help.  I'm thinking rendering tens to hundreds of gigabytes of video in Adobe Premier or something like that.  Other than that I agree it's probably not going to help most people.  By most I mean 99.999%. 
          
