	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          It's interesting -- I was under the impression that RAID 0 was a big boon to normal desktop computer operations.  I think I've even read people say things to that effect right here in this forum.  Go figure. <br>  <br> RAID 1 still has a use in the desktop world, of course.  Given how cheap drives have become, it's not a bad idea to double-up for safety's sake on computers that will hold important development or business data, even temporarily.  But for home users.... can't really see it.  (Wouldn't help you with a virus, for example, so you still gotta do periodic, dated backups to another drive.) 
          
